) narrow and keel-shaped; mesoventrite behind anterior ridge with sharply delimited lateral asetose impressions (

Fig. 
14

; 
ai
); prepectus (

Fig. 
14

; 
pre
) long, posterior portion of mesanepisternum only partly visible in ventral view; mesepimeron not visible in ventral view; mesothorax with deep ventro-lateral fovea at each side (

Fig. 
14

; 
vlf
); mesocoxal projections (

Fig. 
14

; 
mcp
